<DOC><DOCNO> AP891114-0191 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-14-89 2333EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Korea-US     11-14 0166</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Korea-US,0170</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Soldier Killed, Seven Injured in U.S. Army Accident</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   One American soldier and one SouthKorean soldier were killed and seven Americans were injured when aU.S. Army personnel carrier overturned during a training exercise,the Army said Wednesday.   An Army statement said the personnel carrier rolled down a slopeTuesday during manuevers near Camp Casey, north of Seoul. Twosoldiers on the carrier were killed and six were injured in theaccident and a seventh soldier was injured while trying to helpthose in the stricken vehicle, it said.   Officials were investigating the cause of the accident.   Names of the dead and injured were being withheld pendingnotification of next of kin. The carrier belonged to the 4thChemical Company of the U.S. 2nd Infantry Division.   The dead Korean soldier was part of South Korean forces assignedto U.S. units in South Korea.   About 43,000 U.S. troops are based in South Korea under a mutualdefense treaty.</TEXT></DOC>